obfuscation: Now let loyal lines gather round-- The Prince 's foster-mother has been found, yet she will declare to silver clarion 's sound rightful King-- let him forthwith be crowned, she will declare etc; and speak woman speak-- our own serves are all attention, news our own serves seek- This moment mention.
original: Now let the loyal lieges gather round--             The Prince's foster-mother has been found! She will declare, to silver clarion's sound,             The rightful King--let him forthwith be crowned! She will declare, etc. Speak, woman, speak--         We're all attention! The news we seek-           This moment mention.

obfuscation: To america they bring-- His foster-mother; is he the King, or this my brother; as speak woman speak etc.
original: To us they bring--          His foster-mother. Is he the King? Or this my brother? Speak, woman, speak, etc.

obfuscation: Royal Prince was by the King entrusted to my fond care ere I grew former and crusted When traitors came to fly his son reputed My own small boy I deftly substituted!
original: The Royal Prince was by the King entrusted             To my fond care, ere I grew old and crusted;             When traitors came to steal his son reputed,             My own small boy I deftly substituted!

obfuscation: villains fell into the trap completely-- I hid Prince away-- still sleeping sweetly myself called him`` son'' with pardonable shyness-- His name ruin; and behold his Royal Highness; yet lui; and casilda; get out mister; a hit monsieur; yet take that mister; and it 's tit Sir For tat sir!
original: The villains fell into the trap completely--             I hid the Prince away--still sleeping sweetly:             I called him "son" with pardonable slyness--             His name, Luiz! Behold his Royal Highness! Luiz! Casilda! Get out, sir! A hit, sir? Take that, sir! It's tit, sir,  For tat, sir!

obfuscation: When two doughy heroes thunder All international is lost in wonder When such men their temper lose Awful are words they use; and tall sobs small sobs rich snow and needy ones, yet whom are you alluding to; where are you intruding to?
original: When two doughty heroes thunder,         All the world is lost in wonder;               When such men their temper lose,               Awful are the words they use! Tall snobs, small snobs, rich snobs and needy ones! Whom are you alluding to? Where are you intruding to?

obfuscation: Fat sobs thin sobs swell snow and seedy ones, myself rather thinks you err; and to whom do you refer; to you sir, and to me sir; as i do sir, as we will see sir; as myself beer sir, grimace Sir, and look here sir-- face Sir!
original: Fat snobs, thin snobs, swell snobs and seedy ones! I rather think you err. To whom do you refer? To you, sir! To me, sir? I do, sir! We'll see, sir! I jeer, sir! Grimace, sir! Look here, sir-- A face, sir!

obfuscation: In fact, When two heroes once pacific Quarrel the effect 's terrific; and what horrible grimace, what a paralyzing face; and big bombs small bombs etc; he has insulted me and in breath This day our own serves are fighting a duel to the death; and you mean in course by duel A Statutory Duel, and why what is that?
original: When two heroes, once pacific,         Quarrel, the effect's terrific! What a horrible grimace! What a paralysing face! Big bombs, small bombs, etc. He has insulted me, and, in a breath, This day we fight a duel to the death! You mean, of course, by duel A Statutory Duel. Why, what's that?
